Description:
    Generates a Rails migration with the appropriate database columns for Flex attributes.
    This generator maps each Flex attribute type to its required database columns automatically.

Usage:
    bin/rails generate flex:migration NAME [attribute:type attribute:type] [options]

Examples:
    bin/rails generate flex:migration AddPersonalInfoToUsers name:name date_of_birth:memorable_date
    bin/rails generate flex:migration AddAddressesToApplications home_address:address work_address:address
    bin/rails generate flex:migration AddFinancialInfoToReports salary:money tax_id:tax_id

Supported Attribute Types:
    address         - Creates columns: street_line_1, street_line_2, city, state, zip_code (all :string)
    date_range      - Creates columns: start, end (both :date)
    memorable_date  - Creates columns: single :date column
    money           - Creates columns: single :integer column (stores cents)
    name            - Creates columns: first, middle, last (all :string)
    tax_id          - Creates columns: single :string column
    us_date         - Creates columns: single :date column
    year_quarter    - Creates columns: year (:integer), quarter (:integer)

This will create:
    A standard Rails migration file with the appropriate column definitions for each Flex attribute type.
